Serialized Form

  • Package no.fint.event.model

    • Class no.fint.event.model.Event extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • corrId

          java.lang.String corrId
          A unique id for an event. It should be a UUID generated by UUID.randomUUID().toString()

        • action

          java.lang.String action
          This should be the command we wish to execute at the provider or cache. For example it could be GET_ALL_EMPLOYEES

        • status

          Status status
          Status of the event. See Status for more informasjon.

        • time

          long time
          The time of the creation of the event. It should be a Unix timestamp generated by System.currentTimeMillis()

        • orgId

          java.lang.String orgId
          Id of the organization the event is from.

        • source

          java.lang.String source
          The name of the felleskomponent the event is for.

        • client

          java.lang.String client
          The name of the client who generated the event. It should either be the name associated the the API token or CACHE

        • message

          java.lang.String message
          This message should be set if something goes wrong. It should typically describe what went wrong, for example a stack trace or an error message.

        • data

          java.util.List<E> data
          This is the list of payload/data for the event.
          • For inbound events it should be queryfilters or data to be updated.
          • For outbound events it should be the data requested or the status of the updatecommand
